<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
These records represent a new southern limit for this species. All the specimens were small (approx. 4 mm), but they were nearly identical to small specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Nuculanidae" genus="Jupiteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Jupiteria lobula" order="Nuculanida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lobula">Jupiteria lobula</taxonomicName>
from Mexico and also the type specimens. The presence of dead valves at different stations and the distance from previous records suggest that this species is living in Colombia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
